The mother of a 12-year-old girl swept

away by a flash flood was clinging to hope that her daughter was alive but perhaps unable to get home, a family friend said Saturday.
Janice Trigg's daughter, Kerri, was among nearly three dozen still missing Saturday night, two days after the floods hit eastern Ohio.
That's a mother's hope," said the friend, Betty Kreiter, 67.
Kerri had been playing at a friend's house when the one-story home suddenly was washed away in the flood Thursday night.
"I saw my husband go under and get washed away.
